    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-12-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-12-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="61" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d61">
                <head>No. 367.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName corresp="#p_DES1" type="from">Sickles</persName> to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HF1" type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Received December 22, 1872, 4.20
                            p.m.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-12-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 22,
                            1872</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Both houses of Congress have accepted, by decisive majorities, the colonial
                        policy indicated in my telegram of 1st instant. Colonial and finance
                        ministers resigned. Successors in accord with their colleagues and Congress.
                        President of council announced that bill for immediate emancipation would be
                        introduced before holiday recess.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DES1">SICKLES</persName>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
